*bcsub*

(PHP 4, PHP 5, PHP 7)

bcsub â€” Subtract one arbitrary precision number from another

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  bcsub ( string $left_operand , string $right_operand [, int $scale = 0 ] ) :~
  string~

Subtracts the {right_operand} from the {left_operand}.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{left_operand}

  The left operand, as a string.

{right_operand}

  The right operand, as a string.

{ scale}

  This optional parameter is used to set the number of digits after the decimal
  place in the result. If omitted, it will default to the scale set globally
  with the |bcscale| function, or fallback to 0 if this has not been set.

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The result of the subtraction, as a string.

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 bcsub() example

<?php >

  $a = '1.234';
  $b = '5';

  echo bcsub($a, $b);     // -3
  echo bcsub($a, $b, 4);  // -3.7660

<?>

